# Trello Task Auto-Processor

At the START of every interaction, check `TRELLO_TASKS.md` for sections marked `## PENDING`.
If any PENDING tasks exist, immediately begin processing them — do NOT wait for the user to ask.

## 1. Parse the PENDING block

Extract from each block:
- `cardId` — use with Trello MCP to fetch full card details
- `boardId` — use with `set_active_board` (if not "unknown", otherwise discover via `list_boards` + `boardName`)
- `cardName` — card title (for reference)

## 2. Execute the trello-dev-workflow

Since the webhook already identified the card, connect to the Trello MCP and:

1. `set_active_board` with the `boardId` (or find the board by name if ID is unknown)
2. `get_lists` to discover list IDs (To Do, In Progress, Testing, Ready [Developed])
3. `get_card` with the `cardId` and `includeMarkdown: true`
4. Assess the card requirements from its title, description, checklists, and comments
5. Plan the implementation using the TodoWrite tool
6. Implement the changes on a feature branch
7. Validate (lint, type-check, build, tests)
8. Commit and push
9. Move the card to "Ready [Developed]" and add a summary comment

## 3. Mark as processed

After completing all phases, update TRELLO_TASKS.md:
- Change `## PENDING` to `## DONE` for that block

## Rules

- Process ONE card at a time — finish all phases before starting the next
- Never skip validation
- If the card has no actionable dev work, mark DONE and note why
